INSERT INTO `wp_comments` VALUES (5,19,'sandip','sandip.more@rightprocedure.com','','125.18.50.34','2008-12-19 01:33:06','2008-12-19 08:33:06','Hi Prasad, I think process may vary across the cities. In hyderabad bike is not required.\r\nIn my case, In the whole process, only verification officer in police station, asked if I got the bike with me, on saying yes, he didnt ask anything or even didnt verify bike, I think He was just probing for some bribe. btw I explicitly asked RTO officer who handed me NOC, if he need to see the bike, he said no, I sent my bike to pune before getting NOC. In your case, you can just ask some of friends in banglore to inquire at RTO office where your bike is registered. Could you let us know how this thing works in banglore, if you try to get noc, so we can publish it here to help many others who are clueless abt this noc procedure?',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.8.1.6) Gecko/20070725 Firefox/2.0.0.6 webaroo/1.2','',0,0,'N'),(4,19,'prasad','prasad@gmail.com','','125.16.131.20','2008-12-18 13:36:09','2008-12-18 20:36:09','freind,\r\n\r\nis it not possible to go through process without bike as i m in pune now have to get NOC from banglaore?',0,'1','Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 7.0; Windows NT 6.0; SLCC1; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; .NET CLR 3.0.04506)','',0,0,'N'),(6,22,'jvvnmurty','jvvnmurty@gmail.com','http://jvvnmurty.blogspot.com','121.247.67.56','2008-12-30 21:59:41','2008-12-31 04:59:41','Hi,\r\n\r\n  Thanks for u r information.\r\n  I want to stay only for 3 months in pune. Is there any other alternate so that i can use my vehical without any tension.\r\n\r\nRegards,\r\nMurty.',0,'1','Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 6.0; Windows NT 5.1; SV1; (R1 1.6); InfoPath.2)','',0,0,'N'),(7,22,'sandipmore','sandip.more@gmail.com','http://www.sadipmore.com','125.18.50.34','2009-01-06 06:51:13','2009-01-06 13:51:13','hello murthy,\r\n sorry for late reply to your comment. NOC is must for driving non-state vehicle. I think its validity is 6 months. other than that I think you can pay road tax here and drive vehicle peacefully. otherwise there is always risk to get caught by police.',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.8.1.6) Gecko/20070725 Firefox/2.0.0.6 webaroo/1.2','',0,3,'N'),(8,19,'Ayaz','a2zv@hotmail.com','','220.226.16.144','2009-01-12 11:04:55','2009-01-12 18:04:55','Hey Sandip,\r\n Thanks for that detailed information to get NOC from Hyderabad, keep up the good work.\r\nAyaz',0,'1','Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 6.0; Windows NT 5.1; SV1; .NET CLR 1.0.3705; .NET CLR 1.1.4322; .NET CLR 2.0.50727)','',0,0,'N'),(12,166,'Rahul','rahul_kiit@rediffmail.com','','147.29.27.132','2009-01-20 21:37:09','2009-01-21 04:37:09','Hi Ajit/Amit,\r\n\r\nYou must have the NOC to pay the RoadTax. As NOC indiactes this vehicle is not a stolen or any police case on it and when you actually brought the vehicle in the state(this helps in calcullating road tax).\r\nGetting NOC from Karnataks is very easy. It just took me 2 days and there is no charges for it.',0,'1','Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 7.0; Windows NT 5.1; .NET CLR 1.1.4322; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; MS-RTC LM 8; InfoPath.1; .NET CLR 3.0.04506.648; .NET CLR 3.5.21022)','',0,0,'Y'),(10,166,'Ajit','clickah@yahoo.in','http://www.none.com','125.17.114.226','2009-01-15 03:48:35','2009-01-15 10:48:35','Hi Rahul,\r\nThanks for sharing experience with us. I want to know that NOC is required or not if i want to PAY Maharashtra Road Tax.',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.0.5) Gecko/2008120122 Firefox/3.0.5','',0,0,'N'),(11,166,'Amit Sharma','amit0783@gmail.com','','125.17.112.225','2009-01-20 01:41:21','2009-01-20 08:41:21','Hi Rahul,\r\n\r\nCould you please tell me if it is necessary to take the NOC to pay the maharashtra road tax.\r\nWhat if i want to pay the tax only without submitting the NOC becoz i want to stay in  maharshtra say for 1.5 yrs and then want to go back to my own state where i want to use the same bike.\r\nPlease respond to my ID also:- amit.sharma@clsa.com',0,'1','Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 7.0; Windows NT 5.1; .NET CLR 1.1.4322; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; InfoPath.1)','',0,0,'N'),(13,19,'suresh','sureshmstat@gmail.com','','203.78.210.158','2009-01-22 06:20:38','2009-01-22 13:20:38','Hi can anyone help me regarding the NOC, as now i am in mumbai.\r\n\r\nI want NOC from Hyderabad. how to proceed ?.. thankd in advance.. and i need the form number which we have to sketch the chosis number on that form .. ?',0,'1','Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 6.0; Windows NT 5.1; SV1; .NET CLR 1.1.4322; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; .NET CLR 3.0.04506.648; .NET CLR 3.5.21022; InfoPath.2; MS-RTC LM 8)','',0,0,'N'),(14,19,'sandipmore','sandip.more@gmail.com','http://rightprocedure.org','125.18.50.34','2009-01-22 06:37:06','2009-01-22 13:37:06','<a href=\"#comment-13\" rel=\"nofollow\">hey suresh,</a>\r\nI already described the procedure to get the NOC from hyderabad. You can get forms from RTO office. it should be free of cost, form number is either 29 or 30.',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.8.1.6) Gecko/20070725 Firefox/2.0.0.6 webaroo/1.2','',0,3,'N'),(15,22,'Sushant Kumar','sushantb2@yahoo.com','','203.196.206.222','2009-01-28 02:28:20','2009-01-28 09:28:20','Thanks Sandip, for your valuable information on Re registartion of vechile in Pune. Me too brought my car from Jamshedpur to Pune, having NOC from RTO Jamshedpur which is valid for a year. Is NOC sufficient for driving the vechile safely in PUNE(w/o getting caught)',0,'1','Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 6.0; Windows NT 5.1; SV1)','',0,0,'N'),(16,22,'venkat','kvreddy26@gmail.com','','123.201.37.6','2009-01-31 05:56:41','2009-01-31 12:56:41','Thank u sandip for ur detailed information . its very useful',0,'1','Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 6.0; Windows NT 5.1; SV1; .NET CLR 1.1.4322; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; .NET CLR 3.0.04506.30; .NET CLR 3.0.04506.648)','',0,0,'N'),(17,22,'Rajesh','in_goodguy@yahoo.co.uk','','202.144.125.194','2009-02-03 03:06:15','2009-02-03 10:06:15','Sandip that was really a useful information. Can you let us know what is the procedure for claiming back the Life tax paid in the earlier state?\r\n\r\nSushant, I think just NOC would not suffice, if you are planning to stay for a long time there. Also NOC is valid for 90 days only rather than 1 year as you have mentioned. You would need to pay Road tax also. Otherwise the traffic police might trouble you.  Check the below site for more answers:http://www.indiacar.com/askanexpert/browsepas.asp?pg=17',0,'1','Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 7.0; Windows NT 5.1; .NET CLR 1.1.4322)','',0,0,'N'),(23,22,'Johnson','johnson.mathew79@gmail.com','','203.91.207.30','2009-02-06 04:18:31','2009-02-06 11:18:31','Any body guide me.I got transfer to Kochin from Chennai.But I dont have NOC now.So Please let me know how to move forward now with the bike  for safe driving.',0,'1','Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 6.0; Windows NT 5.1; SV1; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; MS-RTC LM 8)','',0,0,'N'),(120,166,'sanjay','sajaykumar.sharma@bt.com','','220.225.64.7','2009-02-09 06:19:21','2009-02-09 13:19:21','Rahul,\r\nI am undergoing the similar phase .Please can you help me \r\n1) NOC is required or not to register in Pune.\r\n2) If no then what is the procedure.\r\n2) I am in pune for 1 yr only so do I need to pay taxes or not.',0,'1','Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 7.0; Windows NT 6.0; SLCC1; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; .NET CLR 3.0.04506; InfoPath.2)','',0,0,'N'),(121,166,'yashpal','yaxhpal@gmail.com','http://www.yashpalmeena.com','121.240.72.205','2009-02-09 07:57:23','2009-02-09 14:57:23','<a href=\"#comment-120\" rel=\"nofollow\">@sanjay </a> \r\nHi Sanjay,\r\n\r\nWhat I figured out from posts on RightProcedure is this:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>1) You definitely need NOC for registering your bike to Pune. NOC indicates no objection from former government body (previous state) i.e., it is not stolen or under any legal issue.</li>\r\n	<li>2) NA</li>\r\n\r\n	<li>3) If you get caught, sure you have to. :twisted:</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\nAlso, checkout these two post by Sandip.\r\n<a href=\"http://www.rightprocedure.org/?p=19\" rel=\"nofollow\">No objection certificate for vehicle transfer</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.rightprocedure.org/?p=22\" rel=\"nofollow\">Transfer of vehicle to Pune from other state</a>\r\n\r\n',0,'1','Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 6.0; Windows NT 5.1; SV1; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; .NET CLR 1.1.4322)','',0,2,'N'),(122,166,'Rahul Saxena','rahul_kiit@rediffmail.com','','117.195.45.97','2009-02-09 09:16:47','2009-02-09 16:16:47','Sanjay,\r\n\r\nIn your case, I will strongly suggest not to drive your vehicle in main roads, incase you get caught, try to escape by paying money else if you go legally they will seize your bike, and ask for complete process.And you don\'t have NOC, so you might come in trouble.',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.0; en-US) AppleWebKit/525.19 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/1.0.154.48 Safari/525.19','',0,0,'Y'),(123,166,'Puneet Gulati','puneetgulatiin@gmail.com','','122.160.81.119','2009-02-11 02:29:03','2009-02-11 09:29:03','Hi rahul, \r\nI am planning to get my bike from New Delhi to Pune.\r\nEarlier i was planning to sell my bike in New Delhi and then buy a second hand bike in Pune. After reading your post i think i should get my bike to pune along with RC, PUC, Invoice, Insurance and then just go and pay the road tax for maharashtra.\r\nSo will this be all i need to do over here??\r\nor anything else needs to be done from my end??',0,'1','Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 7.0; Windows NT 6.0; SV1; SLCC1; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; .NET CLR 3.0.04506; InfoPath.2)','',0,0,'N'),(124,166,'Rahul Saxena','rahul_kiit@rediffmail.com','','117.195.35.170','2009-02-11 07:40:00','2009-02-11 14:40:00','Hi Puneet,\r\nYou have not mentioned NOC, which is must to drive vehicle in the other state.\r\nMine process was simple as I get caught by traffic police and they sent it for process, if you go by yourself to pay the tax, I think they will ask you to take the Maharashtra number, which is bit complicated process. \r\nI suggest you to bring your bike with NOC and go through the process without any agent.',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.0; en-US) AppleWebKit/525.19 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/1.0.154.48 Safari/525.19','',0,0,'Y'),(125,166,'Rajorshi','rajorshi1981@gmail.com','','160.83.96.81','2009-02-13 10:52:53','2009-02-13 17:52:53','Hi Rahul,\r\nMy prob. is a little diff. I bought a Pulsar early last year and immediately sent it to my bro @ Nagpur as he was in urgent need. The NOC from Bangalore RTO was regretably not obtained and the bike shipped straight-away to Nagpur. Now he\'s having trouble with traffic cops @ Nagpur, and so wants the NOC so that he may register the bike @ Maharashtra. Problem is : Bike is PHYSICALLY in Nagpur, so how do I get NOC from B\'lore RTO? Either the RTO officials or the police (during verification) will probably ask for physical inspection of the bike before they issue the NOC document. So ..... is there anyway to get the NOC or is this screwed up beyond repair?  Thanks.',0,'1','Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 6.0; Windows NT 5.1; SV1; .NET CLR 1.1.4322; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; .NET CLR 3.0.04506.30)','',0,0,'N'),(126,166,'Rahul','rahul_kiit@rediffmail.com','','147.29.27.132','2009-02-15 23:37:45','2009-02-16 06:37:45','Hi Rajorshi,\r\nMy experience is that for applying NOC you don\'t have show your bike, but you must need the chasis print (pencil). What I suggest you to get the 5-6 copies of Form-28(will be good if you get it from bangalore) and take the chasis print on them.\r\nI also helped couple of my friends to apply the NOC from Bangalore/Pune but no where it is asked to show your bike/car.',0,'1','Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 7.0; Windows NT 5.1; .NET CLR 1.1.4322; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; MS-RTC LM 8; InfoPath.1; .NET CLR 3.0.04506.648; .NET CLR 3.5.21022)','',0,0,'Y'),(127,22,'Sudeep','sudeep160@yahoo.co.in','','59.99.52.39','2009-02-16 23:54:30','2009-02-17 06:54:30','Hi,\r\n     My brother-in-law bought a Pulsar 180 Dtsi on 13 July 2007 in Bangalore. He shifted to Pune in September 2007. He took a NOC from Bangalore RTO in the favour of Solapur RTO (instead of Pune RTO). Now the bike is in Pune. The bike insurance has expired and not renewed yet.\r\n1)As the NOC has expired, will he have to go Bangalore again for New NOC?\r\n2)Is it possible to re-register the bike with Pune RTO though the NOC is in favour of Solapur RTO?\r\n3) How to apply for Refund of Road Tax from Bangalore RTO?\r\n\r\nPlease reply.\r\nSudeep.',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.0.6) Gecko/2009011913 Firefox/3.0.6','',0,0,'N'),(129,22,'Sudeep','sudeep160@yahoo.co.in','','59.99.52.148','2009-02-17 23:33:34','2009-02-18 06:33:34','<a href=\"#comment-7\" rel=\"nofollow\">@sandipmore</a> \r\nPlease answer my comment, Sandip.',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.0.6) Gecko/2009011913 Firefox/3.0.6','',0,0,'N'),(130,22,'sandipmore','sandip.more@gmail.com','http://rightprocedure.org','121.240.72.205','2009-02-17 23:53:20','2009-02-18 06:53:20','hi sudeep, renew your bike insurance, it is must. I think you shouldnt have to get noc again. it should work and for in favour of solapur or pune, may be some extra affidavit you need to add. Just go to rto and start the procedure, for refund of road tax, I myself want to know abt this.',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.8.1.6) Gecko/20070725 Firefox/2.0.0.6 webaroo/1.2','',0,3,'N'),(135,166,'Rajorshi','rajorshi1981@gmail.com','','160.83.96.82','2009-02-18 12:56:56','2009-02-18 19:56:56','Thanks Rahul. I\'ll try that. Found another site which may be of some use to Karnataka folk :  http://rto.kar.nic.in/list-procedures.htm',0,'1','Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 6.0; Windows NT 5.1; SV1; .NET CLR 1.1.4322)','',0,0,'N');
