formation about tasks, give initial cues and if possible, key contact details, to start working. Information will be about various things you need to carry out in normal life, like getting gas connection, getting internet connection, getting licenses for various work, claiming health insurance. As you search on internet or visit government websites, you wont find this information, some times you do find it but its not useful always. We just want to work towards that goal of getting first hand, right information about how to approach in doing certain things, avoid middlemen, avoid unnecessary visits to various offices wasting your precious time and energy and at worst on waiting on customer support calls.\r\n\r\nWe do not claim that we will succeed in achieving the goal or be able to give solutions to all the problems, people face. But we thought, lets start putting this kind of information available on internet.\r\n\r\nAs per our philosophy, Primary motive of this venture is not to earn money, but yearn for creating a best source of information in Indian context. In this quest to present the information in best way possible, We have took decision of not putting advertises around primary content.\r\n\r\nHope we able to present to you all the information helpful to you. You can submit your problems to us.\r\nWish us all the best in our honest efforts !!!','Introduction',0,'','publish','open','closed','','introduction','','','2010-01-12 00:06:28','2010-01-12 07:06:28','',0,'http://www.rightprocedure.com/?page_id=5',0,'page','',0),(6,1,'2008-12-03 10:18:37','2008-12-03 17:18:37','','Introduction',0,'','inherit','open','open','','5-revision','','','2008-12-03 10:18:37','2008-12-03 17:18:37','',5,'http://www.rightprocedure.com/?p=6',0,'revision','',0),(7,1,'2008-12-03 10:18:51','2008-12-03 17:18:51','','Introduction',0,'','inherit','open','open','','5-revision-2','','','2008-12-03 10:18:51','2008-12-03 17:18:51','',5,'http://www.rightprocedure.com/?p=7',0,'revision','',0),(8,1,'2008-12-03 10:19:28','2008-12-03 17:19:28','','Introduction',0,'','inherit','open','open','','5-revision-3','','','2008-12-03 10:19:28','2008-12-03 17:19:28','',5,'http://www.rightprocedure.com/?p=8',0,'revision','',0),(9,1,'2008-12-03 10:21:19','2008-12-03 17:21:19','This is the initial list of topics, We want to publish on this website. if you would know anything specific about following topics or you know about any new topics which you would like to hear from us. Please let us know.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"color: #003300;\">How to obtain vehicle NOC </span></strong>\r\n<blockquote><strong><span style=\"color: #003300;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; color: #000000;\">A guide to get No Objection Certificate.\r\n</span></span></strong></blockquote>\r\n<span style=\"color: #003300;\"><strong>How to re-register vehicle</strong></span>\r\n<blockquote>Describes the right procedure to get your vehicle re-registered with different state.</blockquote>\r\n<strong><span style=\"color: #003300;\">Getting NOC for car to drive for limited period in Mumbai</span></strong>\r\n<blockquote>A guide to get NOC for limited period in Mumbai.</blockquote>\r\n<span style=\"color: #003300;\"><strong> Claiming health insurance</strong></span>\r\n<blockquote>How to claim your health insurance right way?</blockquote>\r\n<span style=\"color: #003300;\"><strong>Adopting a child</strong></span>\r\n<blockquote>Are you thinking of adopting a child? Nothing can be as noble as this! But how will you proceed? Here is you answer.</blockquote>\r\n<span style=\"color: #003300;\"><strong>Lost debit card / credit card</strong></span>\r\n<blockquote>What? You are not going to do anything about it. Don\'t be fooled, you don\'t want your bank account be hacked by some miscreants. What you going to do then? Here is right procedure to proceed with such situation.</blockquote>\r\n<span style=\"color: #003300;\"><strong>Buying an old flat</strong></span>\r\n<blockquote><span style=\"white-space:pre\"> </span>How should you go buying an old flat from someone/through someone?</blockquote>\r\n<span style=\"color: #003300;\"><strong>Buying an old independent house</strong></span>\r\n<blockquote><span style=\"color: #003300;\"><strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400; color: #000000;\">Home is home. Everyone wants to have his/her own domicile. But home searchers have their natural predator called Real Estate Agents. And worse is when you are in hand of a wrong agent. Here is how you go buying your sweet home.</span></strong></span></blockquote>\r\n<strong><span style=\"color: #003300;\">US Visa interview</span></strong>\r\n<blockquote>What should you prepare for? How difficult is it? What are the required things? Need answers, here are they.\r\n </blockquote>\r\n<strong><span style=\"color: #003300;\">Trademarking</span></strong>\r\n<blockquote>how to apply for a trade mark in respect of particular goods or services?</blockquote>','Topics',0,'','publish','closed','closed','','topics','','','2009-07-05 18:37:37','2009-07-06 01:37:37','',0,'http://www.rightprocedure.com/?page_id=9',2,'page','',0),(10,1,'2008-12-03 10:20:35','2008-12-03 17:20:35','','Future Topics',0,'','inherit','open','open','','9-revision','','','2008-12-03 10:20:35','2008-12-03 17:20:35','',9,'http://www.rightprocedure.com/?p=10',0,'revision','',0),(11,1,'2008-12-03 10:21:12','2008-12-03 17:21:12','','Topics',0,'','inherit','open','open','','9-revision-2','','','2008-12-03 10:21:12','2008-12-03 17:21:12','',9,'http://www.rightprocedure.com/?p=11',0,'revision','',0),(12,1,'2008-12-03 10:21:19','2008-12-03 17:21:19','','Topics',0,'','inherit','open','open','','9-revision-3','','','2008-12-03 10:21:19','2008-12-03 17:21:19','',9,'http://www.rightprocedure.com/?p=12',0,'revision','',0),(13,1,'2008-12-03 10:06:08','2008-12-03 17:06:08','','About',0,'','inherit','open','open','','2-revision-3','','','2008-12-03 10:06:08','2008-12-03 17:06:08','',2,'http://www.rightprocedure.com/?p=13',0,'revision','',0),(14,1,'2008-12-03 10:24:34','2008-12-03 17:24:34','','About',0,'','inherit','open','open','','2-revision-4','','','2008-12-03 10:24:34','2008-12-03 17:24:34','',2,'http://www.rightprocedure.com/?p=14',0,'revision','',0),(31,1,'2008-12-03 13:04:27','2008-12-03 20:04:27','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">So after getting NOC from Hyderabad, Andhra pradesh, Next step was to re-register bike in Pune, I needed to deal with RTO, Pune, Maharashtra, Compare to hyd RTO, I found pune RTO to be much clumsier, full of agents, no PRO to get information with. still able to get information about what to do.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> When I went to RTO, I was surrounded by Agents, who were demandeing 2000 Rs apart from all other taxes. I think doing it yourself should be much better as it does gives you experience of working with government offices. also after doing all hard work while getting NOC from hyd, I thought this should be miniscule task. so Wanted to do it myself.</p>\r\n\r\nafter inquiring further, I came to know that person called Mr. Pazze handles all matters about vehicle outside Maharashtra, So I went to him and He handed me a document listing all the following. He is key person in carrying out this whole work.\r\nHe will describe you whole procedure with very cool head and seems to be quite nice guy.\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>NOC from original state where vehicle belongs(in my case Hyd, AP). 2 copies original</li>\r\n	<li>RC book original, registration card</li>\r\n	<li>Vehicle Insurance</li>\r\n	<li>Invoice receipt - vehicle purchase dealer receipt</li>\r\n	<li>Entry tax , in case when you bring the vehicle before 30 months of registration date.</li>\r\n	<li>Address proof where you are staying currently with photo</li>\r\n	<li>Affidavit of non-stolen vehicle by registered owner</li>\r\n	<li>Form. No 26,27, 20,33 . you will get these forms free at rto.</li>\r\n	<li>Pencil chassis print - 5 original</li>\r\n	<li>NOC from Police Commisioner pune.</li>\r\n	<li>Registration fee- 320</li>\r\n	<li>7 % for invoice cost as registration</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n- you can refund prev paid tax by applying at hyd.\r\n\r\nHe asked me to get the affidavit on 20 Rs stamp paper. so I went outside, was inquiring abt affidavit, one person demanded me Rs 200 per affidavit and I asked some other person he was taking 100 Rs so I asked him to do the work. so while having conversation with him, I came to know that He also had reregistered his vehicle but through agents and in turn paid quite big amount to get the work done, he was happy knowing that I am doing work myself not through RTO agent.\r\n\r\nIn pt. 10. to get NOC from Police Commisioner pune., you need a letter from RTO.\r\nYou will get this letter from Mr. Pazze, after showing him all the above docs, after verifying docs, he will give you a letter from RTO to Commissioner of police,\r\nYou need to give it in Commissioner of police office with xerox of NOC from hyd, and residential proof. and after 7 working days you will get the NOC from Pune police. The concerned person is Mr. Chavan. He will issue you NOC in 10 minutes, if everything is ok.\r\n\r\nThen you need to submit all of above docs to Mr. Pazze and he will check the things and\r\nyou need to get assessement done from counter 30/31( i think). then after getting how much amount you need to pay, you need to pay tax at counter 23/24 (i think..). and then re submit docs along with receipt of tax payment to Mr. Pazze. He will ask you to see him after 1 and half months.\r\n\r\nso till now, it took arnd 2 weeks to get this much work done.\r\n\r\nSo finally I got my docs back from RTO officer, after that I had to go to alandi office to acquire a sign from RTO officer who checks the vehicles and gives you back the paper which takes 1 hours.\r\n\r\nNow I need to give this docs back to RTO and get New maharashtra registration number and then apply for tax refund from hyderabad office.\r\n\r\nemail me if you any further queries.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">I have written this blog in 2007. RTO procedure might have underwent some changes. if any of you go to RTO and find something is changed, I do request you to add comment or post link to your blog to help people who read this blog.</p>','Transfer of vehicle to pune from other state ',0,'Transfer of vehicle to pune from other state and re-registration of vehicle in pune ','inherit','open','open','','22-revision-5','','','2008-12-03 13:04:27','2008-12-03 20:04:27','',22,'http://www.rightprocedure.com/?p=31',0,'revision','',0),(30,1,'2008-12-03 12:58:57','2008-12-03 19:58:57','So after getting NOC from Hyderabad, Andhra pradesh, Next step was to re-register bike in Pune,\r\nI needed to deal with RTO, Pune, Maharashtra, Compare to hyd RTO, I found pune RTO to be much clumsier, full of agents, no PRO to get information with. still able to get information about what to do.\r\n\r\nwhen I went to RTO, I was surrounded by Agents, who were demandeing 2000 Rs apart from all other taxes. I think doing it yourself should be much better as it does gives you experience of working with government offices. also after doing all hard work while getting NOC from hyd, I thought this should be miniscule task. so Wanted to do it myself.\r\n\r\nafter inquiring further, I came to know that person called Mr. Pazze handles all matters about vehicle outside Maharashtra, So I went to him and He handed me a document listing all the following. He is key person in carrying out this whole work.\r\nHe will describe you whole procedure with very cool head and seems to be quite nice guy.\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>NOC from original state where vehicle belongs(in my case Hyd, AP). 2 copies original</li>\r\n	<li>RC book original, registration card</li>\r\n	<li>Vehicle Insurance</li>\r\n	<li>Invoice receipt - vehicle purchase dealer receipt</li>\r\n	<li>Entry tax , in case when you bring the vehicle before 30 months of registration date.</li>\r\n	<li>Address proof where you are staying curr