 a Corporate medical insurance, so what would be the ideal way to go about it.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">Okay I say “go about it” and not “claiming it” because you do not necessarily claim the money when you have a medical or health insurance.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">There are two ways to “go about it”; I was enlightened, which are as follows:</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.5in; text-indent: -0.25in; mso-list: l2 level1 lfo2;\"><span style=\"font-family: Wingdings; mso-fareast-font-family: Wingdings; mso-bidi-font-family: Wingdings;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Ø</span><span style=\"font: 7pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">  </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">Cashless- You can avail this method only if you are getting the patient admitted to one of hospitals that have a tie up with your Insurance Company.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">This is the roughly the procedure. </span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">Our doctor suggested surgery. He said he would want to operate my mother on the following Monday. He said that the whole expense would be approximately Rs. 50,000. I had roughly one and a half day at hand. I was not tensed, I will tell you the reason after I tell you about the pre-surgery insurance formalities.</span></p>\n\n<ul style=\"margin-top: 0in;\" type=\"disc\">\n	<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo1;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">Doctor has to sign the cashless claim form and write about the illness, the line of treatment and the purpose of surgery.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.5in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">In this whole procedure the <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\">Cashless card</strong> <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\">is a must</strong>. Do not buy the story of your Insurance Agent telling to mention your employee id. It doesn’t work always. </span></p>\n\n<ul style=\"margin-top: 0in;\" type=\"disc\">\n	<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo1;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">The form has to be submitted to the Insurance department of the Hospital which they fax to the insurance company only and only if the hospital has a tie up.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.5in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">It is advisable that you constantly keep in touch with your agent and take the 24 hour toll free number of the Insurance Company so that you can call and find out if they have received the fax from the hospital. Most of the times the hospital insurance wing doesn’t send it so make sure!</span></p>\n\n<ul style=\"margin-top: 0in;\" type=\"disc\">\n	<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo1;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">The Insurance Company only sends a fraction of the amount that the hospital claims. The rest of it comes after the discharge report is sent to them.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">Now let me narrate my story. </span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">I decided to get the cashless form signed by the doctor and submit it to the Insurance wing of the hospital. However when I went to submit the form I realized the person in charge of it was not there for the day, yet I was given the assurance that things would be looked after. </span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">Even after the assurance, I got the toll free number and the person on charge of the Hospital insurance wing. I kept on calling both the places and understood that either one of them was not being sincere. The hospital kept on telling me that they have faxed the form and Insurance Company kept on telling me that they haven’t.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">The next day was Sunday. All the administrative offices in the hospital remained closed that day. My mother was to be operated early morning; I paid Rs. 10,000 as security so that the doctors could at least start. </span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Moral: Get the cashless approval well in time to avoid paying the security deposit which you will face trouble to get back from the hospital authorities.</span></span></strong></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">It was a conservative surgery and we could take mom back home the same day. Now we faced the real trial.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">The hospital bill was in total Rs.66, 627. It wasn’t that big a deal. I called up my Insurance agent for the nth time that day and he told me that if I don’t get the formalities done within 5 pm in the evening, we would have tough time. </span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">The hospital would not keep the patient because it would have prepared the final bill, neither would they let release her since they would not get the Insurance Claim approval from the Insurance Company after the regular working hours.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">So here started the running around from the doctor’s cabin to the Insurance wing to my mother’s ward. The doctor had too many patients to take care of (understandable), yet he came for his regular ward visits and Okayed mom for discharge. </span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">The discharge approval was sent to the Insurance wing and then after approximately 50 odd calls to the Insurance Company Call Center and bickering with the Insurance wing of the hospital, we finally received the fax approving the Rs.66,000. </span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Health Insurance or medical Insurance only covers expenses related to the health. They do not pay any administrative charges, like the food in the hospital, at times gloves that the doctors wear when checking or operating the patient. So that can run up to a nominal amount. <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\">It ideally should be 30% of your overall expenses.</strong></span></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.5in; text-indent: -0.25in; mso-list: l2 level1 lfo2;\"><span style=\"font-family: Wingdings; mso-fareast-font-family: Wingdings; mso-bidi-font-family: Wingdings;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Ø</span><span style=\"font: 7pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">  </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">Reimbursement- Reimbursement works if the hospital where you want to get the treatment done is not one of the listed hospitals with the Insurance Company.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.5in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">It basically involves you paying the money upfront and then claiming it from the Insurance Company (getting the reimbursement).</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.5in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">I got involved in the process of reimbursement when I tried to claim the post hospitalization expenses and the Chemotherapy sessions. </span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.5in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">Let me tell you the way which you can ideally follow when claiming for a reimbursement:</span></p>\n\n<ul style=\"margin-top: 0in;\" type=\"disc\">\n	<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo3;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">Keep all your documents carefully. The bills, prescriptions, reports and discharge certificates are essential for you to claim any hospitalization.</span></li>\n	<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo3;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">Insurance Company requires the originals. So definitely keep a photocopy of the originals of your documents for your reference. However if you ask they are bound to give you back the reports, after you the claim procedure over.</span></li>\n	<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo3;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">In case of a deficiency of any document that is important for your claim, the Insurance Company compulsorily has to inform you about the requisite.</span></li>\n	<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo3;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">The money should reach you within 21 days (this can vary with the Insurance Company).</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">It is important to understand that it is integral to send reports of the tests for which you send a bill. The report is as important as the bill to establish the credibility of the claim. </span></span></strong></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">Do not expect for the entire to be reimbursed that you have claimed because administrative charges are deducted.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">In my case the agent didn’t inform me about the deficiency neither did the claim come within 21 days. I got it after 44 long days. This situation arose in spite of me calling the agent incessantly; in fact it was as regular as every morning.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">Another important thing that goes unnoticed most of the times is that the hospital <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\">charges almost become double when you avail cashless</strong>. I got to know it when my mom was going through her chemotherapy sessions. We availed for cashless for her first session and the bill was Rs.39,000. On the other hand when we started paying cash, it came down to Rs. 22,000.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">So I wish you all the luck!</span></p>','How to claim Medical/Health Insurance',0,'','inherit','open','open','','73-revision','','','2008-12-09 06:36:54','2008-12-09 13:36:54','',73,'http://www.rightprocedure.com/?p=74',0,'revision','',0),(75,3,'2008-12-09 05:58:35','2008-12-09 12:58:35','<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a class=\"highslide-image\" onclick=\"return hs.expand(this, {captionId:\'caption_1228340546883\'});\" href=\"http://www.rightprocedure.com/wp-content/uploads/2008/12/rightWay.gif\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" style=\"height: 150px;\" title=\"Click to enlarge\" src=\"http://www.rightprocedure.com/wp-content/uploads/2008/12/rightWay.gif\" alt=\"image\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>At Right Procedure, We are going to try our best to put out information, which will give people first hand information abt tasks, give them initial cues and if possible, key contact details,\r\nto start doing things. Always you have option to outsource your work to agents which are ever ready to work out such a tasks. I am not anyway against this type of work. but Again some kind\r\nof corruption does crept from these small things which doesnt matter to you but can form certain big scams at back end or from other perspectives in which these agents do work.</div>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"></p>\r\n\r\nThis is non-profit venture, we are not even putting advertising on our site. As primary motive is not to earn money from this initiative but to create a useful source of information for People on Internet.\r\nas being the regular web surfer, I did feel that content gets cluttered when advertises added to content. though there will be donation link where you can donate, if you can, to let us buy better infrastructure to host this website.','Introduction',0,'','inherit','open','open','','5-revision-23','','','2008-12-09 05:58:35','2008-12-09 12:58:35','',5,'http://www.rightprocedure.com/?p=75',0,'revision','',0),(245,3,'2009-07-22 02:56:47','2009-07-22 09:56:47','<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><em>posted by: </em><strong>Sandip More</strong></p>\r\n\r\nI always believe in working out most of the things myself. When its sensitive thing like filing of one\'s income tax returns, you want to be extra cautious as generally its not advisable to share your finances with some other person when you can do it yourself.\r\n\r\nSince last two years, I was trying to file income tax returns online using Indian income tax departments website, I used to start quite enthusiastically but ends up in unsuccessful attempt. as the process was quite complex, most of the terms were unknown to me. I always believed that they should outsource it to someone. and In the end I used to outsource it to some CA.\r\n\r\nThis month we have to file income tax returns, I was in Noida away from so. I was thinking of sending documents Form16 back home and ask my brother to file returns through some CA. but may be the, Hope is the best thing in the world.  I turned to Google and searched for online filing in India.  I got to <a href=\"http://taxsmile.com\">Taxsmile</a>\r\n\r\nWebsite looked good, so I thought I would give a try as It looked better to me than kind of time I spend in Indian income tax website understanding things. I registered. registration process was simple.\r\n\r\nafter logging in, It looks very obvious process, they took me stap by step. taking personal information first.\r\n\r\nthen taking me to form where I can fill my tax details it was quite simple, exactly similler to my Form 16.\r\n\r\nI found everything pretty easy. I opted for digital signature. I just need to take application form from TaxSmile, paste photo on it and  attach PAN card xerox, address proof xerox to it. and I am done.\r\n\r\naddition to filing normal returns on Tax deduction at source on salary , it also asks for incomes from other sources like Stocks, MFs, Bank Account interests and calculates tax for you which is not included in Form 16 given  by your company and helps you to file IT returns properly and correctly to save you from future headaches.\r\n\r\nThey have good FAQ and interesting planning tools to calculate taxes.\r\n\r\nevery system has some flaws so this one too have. Actually getting documents attested is pretty good headache, instead one will go to CA. purpose of online filing, if one understand, is to do everything online and no paper work. so I think somehow they should remove this documents thing.\r\n\r\nI was getting sms\'s from MyItReturn.com, claiming they would file your income tax in 15 minutes but again\r\n\r\nthey have adoption problem, you need to download a ITR-V form and need to submit it to incometax office yourself which is kind of painful. if you anyway have to go to Income tax office, you can file your returns there directly.\r\n\r\nso still online filing of returns has scope of lots of improvement.\r\n\r\nDisclaimer: This site is not anyway related to or benefitted from Taxsmile directly or indirectly. We are not advertizing Taxsmile.','Online filing of income tax returns',0,'','inherit','open','open','','220-revision-5','','','2009-07-22 02:56:47','2009-07-22 09:56:47','',220,'http://www.rightprocedure.org/?p=245',0,'revision','',0),(244,3,'2010-01-12 00:04:39','2010-01-12 07:04:39','<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a class=\"highslide-image\" onclick=\"return hs.expand(this, {captionId:\'caption_1228340546883\'});\" href=\"http://www.rightprocedure.org/wp-content/uploads/2008/12/rightWay.gif\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" style=\"height: 150px;\" title=\"Click to enlarge\" src=\"http://www.rightprocedure.com/wp-content/uploads/2008/12/rightWay.gif\" alt=\"image\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><em>Mavens are \"information specialists\", or \"people we rely upon to connect us with new information.\"They accumulate knowledge, especially about the marketplace, and know how to share it with others.\r\n</em>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><em>-- </em><strong>Tipping Point</strong></p>\r\n\r\nYes, Maven is best term is what rightprocedure wants to be, instead of Marketplace, for us it\'s LifePlace,\r\n\r\nAt Right Procedure, We are going to try our best to collect the information from various sources and put out it on web, which will avail primary source of information about tasks, give initial cues and if possible, key contact details, to start working. Information will be about various things you need to carry out in normal life, like getting gas connection, getting internet connection, getting licenses for various work, claiming health insurance. As you search on internet or visit government websites, you wont find this information, some times you do find it but its not useful always. We just want to work towards that goal of getting first hand, right information about how to approach in doing certain things, avoid middlemen, avoid unnecessary visits to various offices wasting your precious time and energy and at worst on waiting on customer support calls.\r\n\r\nWe do not claim that we will succeed in achieving the goal or be able to give solutions to all the problems, people face. But we thought, lets start putting this kind of information available on internet.\r\n\r\nAs per our philosophy, Primary motive of this venture is not to earn money, but yearn for creating a best source of information in Indian context. In this quest to present the information in best way possible, We have took decision of not putting advertises around primary content.\r\n\r\nHope we able to present to you all the information helpful to you. You can submit your problems to us.\r\nWish us all the best in our honest efforts !!!','Introduction',0,'','inherit','open','open','','5-revision-41','','','2010-01-12 00:04:39','2010-01-12 07:04:39','',5,'http://www.rightprocedure.org/?p=244',0,'revision','',0),(102,4,'2008-12-15 06:06:31','2008-12-15 13:06:31','<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><em>Posted by:</em> <strong> Pawan kumar Neelam\r\n</strong>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">PAN means <strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">P</span></strong>ermanent <strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">A</span></strong>ccount <strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">N</span></strong>umber. Being an Indian citizen you need it for filing your tax returns, and mandatory for any high value financial transaction, in equity market and In many cases can be used as Identity card.</p>\r\n\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n	<li class=\"MsoNormal\">There are 3 ways to get a PAN card - Firstly one can contact any agent (mostly he is the person who handle your tax related matters) Secondly one apply for PAN card online and pay the amount online thru credit card, Demand Draft or thru Cheque and third-way is do it traditional way i.e. fill the form yourself and submit it.</li>\r\n	<li class=\"MsoNormal\">If you decide on applying for pan card online then <a title=\"Application for PAN through Online Services\" href=\"https://tin.tin.nsdl.com/pan/index.html \" target=\"_blank\">this site</a> should help you for the same. There you can find how to apply for new PAN, reprint of PAN card, Correction in PAN details, Status track for PAN application</li>\r\n	<li class=\"MsoNormal\">Thirdly if you want to fill the application yourself and submit it then next few suggestion should be helpful for you - Firstly you need to get the PAN application form i.e. FORM49A One can get it form any income Tax department, IT services department, or any INCOME TAX PAN SERVICES UNIT i.e. any UTIISL centers which are sub centers been outsourced by the IT department. OR one can download the form <a title=\"Downloadables PAN\" href=\"http://www.tin-nsdl.com/DownloadsPAN.asp\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</li>\r\n	<li class=\"MsoNormal\">The Main points one should keep in mind while filling up the IT form is <strong>it should be filled in capitals, </strong>as a proof one should attach<strong> Proof of Identity </strong>i.e. any identification proof having photo and is authorized. For that you can attach<strong> Drivers License photo copy, college ID, or work ID. </strong>Then<strong> </strong>you have to attach<strong> photocopy of any address proof like ration card, Telephone/electricity bill in your name. And two photographs.</strong></li>\r\n	<li class=\"MsoNormal\">One will also need to write ward number/range/income tax assessing officer number (which you can find from the copy of the acknowledgement of the last return filed.) If you do not have that, you will have to ask your income tax department in your city, and they will give you the ward number on the form. This <a title=\"Services :: PAN :: AO Code\" href=\"http://www.tin-nsdl.com/PANaocode.asp\" target=\"_blank\">site </a> may help you for further assistance.</li>\r\n	<li class=\"MsoNormal\">After filling the form hardest part is finding the office where to fill the form. Not all the IT offices accept the forms. I am attaching the following link which should help you locate the nearest IT Service Center near your city.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">One thing you should bear in mind if you happen to submit the FORM49A at any IT Service Center run by UTIISL then you need to buy the forms from there itself as those form have a serial numbers and they wont accept any forms which does not have their series number printed on them. All forms downloaded does not have the series number.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Helpful links:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n<div class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a title=\"Department of Revenue, Ministry of Finance, Government of India\" href=\" http://www.incometaxindia.gov.in\" target=\"_blank\">Income Tax Department of India</a></div></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n<div class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a title=\"UTI Technology Services Limited - UTITSL Home\" href=\"http://%3ca%20href=%22http/www.utiisl.co.in/%22%3E%3CFONT%20face=%22Times%20New%20Roman%22%20size=3%3Ehttp:/www.utiisl.co.in\" target=\"_blank\">UTI Technology Services</a></div></li>\r\n	<li>\r\