nstantly keep in touch with your agent and take the 24 hour toll free number of the Insurance Company so that you can call and find out if they have received the fax from the hospital. Most of the times the hospital insurance wing doesn’t send it so make sure!</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"margin-top: 0in;\" type=\"disc\">\r\n	<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo1;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">The Insurance Company only sends a fraction of the amount that the hospital claims. The rest of it comes after the discharge report is sent to them.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">Now let me narrate my story. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">I decided to get the cashless form signed by the doctor and submit it to the Insurance wing of the hospital. However when I went to submit the form I realized the person in charge of it was not there for the day, yet I was given the assurance that things would be looked after. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">Even after the assurance, I got the toll free number and the person on charge of the Hospital insurance wing. I kept on calling both the places and understood that either one of them was not being sincere. The hospital kept on telling me that they have faxed the form and Insurance Company kept on telling me that they haven’t.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">The next day was Sunday. All the administrative offices in the hospital remained closed that day. My mother was to be operated early morning; I paid Rs. 10,000 as security so that the doctors could at least start. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Moral: Get the cashless approval well in time to avoid paying the security deposit which you will face trouble to get back from the hospital authorities.</span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">It was a conservative surgery and we could take mom back home the same day. Now we faced the real trial.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">The hospital bill was in total Rs.66, 627. It wasn’t that big a deal. I called up my Insurance agent for the nth time that day and he told me that if I don’t get the formalities done within 5 pm in the evening, we would have tough time. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">The hospital would not keep the patient because it would have prepared the final bill, neither would they let release her since they would not get the Insurance Claim approval from the Insurance Company after the regular working hours.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">So here started the running around from the doctor’s cabin to the Insurance wing to my mother’s ward. The doctor had too many patients to take care of (understandable), yet he came for his regular ward visits and Okayed mom for discharge. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">The discharge approval was sent to the Insurance wing and then after approximately 50 odd calls to the Insurance Company Call Center and bickering with the Insurance wing of the hospital, we finally received the fax approving the Rs.66,000. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Health Insurance or medical Insurance only covers expenses related to the health. They do not pay any administrative charges, like the food in the hospital, at times gloves that the doctors wear when checking or operating the patient. So that can run up to a nominal amount. <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\">It ideally should be 30% of your overall expenses.</strong></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; line-height: 115%;\">Reimbursement</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: small;\">- Reimbursement works if the hospital where you want to get the treatment done is not one of the listed hospitals with the Insurance Company.</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">It basically involves you paying the money upfront and then claiming it from the Insurance Company (getting the reimbursement).</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">I got involved in the process of reimbursement when I tried to claim the post hospitalization expenses and the Chemotherapy sessions. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">Let me tell you the way which you can ideally follow when claiming for a reimbursement:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.75in; text-indent: -0.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2;\"><span style=\"font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">·</span><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\"> </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">Keep all your documents carefully. The bills, prescriptions, reports and discharge certificates are essential for you to claim any hospitalization.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.75in; text-indent: -0.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2;\"><span style=\"font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">·</span><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\"> </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">Insurance Company requires the originals. So definitely keep a photocopy of the originals of your documents for your reference. However if you ask they are bound to give you back the reports, after you the claim procedure over.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.75in; text-indent: -0.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2;\"><span style=\"font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">·</span><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\"> </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">In case of a deficiency of any document that is important for your claim, the Insurance Company compulsorily has to inform you about the requisite.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.75in; text-indent: -0.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2;\"><span style=\"font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">·</span><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\"> </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">The money should reach you within 21 days (this can vary with the Insurance Company).</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">It is important to understand that it is integral to send reports of the tests for which you send a bill. The report is as important as the bill to establish the credibility of the claim. </span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">Do not expect for the entire to be reimbursed that you have claimed because administrative charges are deducted.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">In my case the agent didn’t inform me about the deficiency neither did the claim come within 21 days. I got it after 44 long days. This situation arose in spite of me calling the agent incessantly; in fact it was as regular as every morning.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">Another important thing that goes unnoticed most of the times is that the hospital <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\">charges almost become double when you avail cashless</strong>. I got to know it when my mom was going through her chemotherapy sessions. We availed for cashless for her first session and the bill was Rs.39,000. On the other hand when we started paying cash, it came down to Rs. 22,000.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">So I wish you all the luck!</span></p>','How to claim Medical/Health Insurance',0,'','inherit','open','open','','73-revision-6','','','2008-12-09 07:51:06','2008-12-09 14:51:06','',73,'http://www.rightprocedure.com/?p=88',0,'revision','',0),(85,3,'2008-12-09 06:49:46','2008-12-09 13:49:46','<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a class=\"highslide-image\" onclick=\"return hs.expand(this, {captionId:\'caption_1228340546883\'});\" href=\"http://www.rightprocedure.com/wp-content/uploads/2008/12/rightWay.gif\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" style=\"height: 150px;\" title=\"Click to enlarge\" src=\"http://www.rightprocedure.com/wp-content/uploads/2008/12/rightWay.gif\" alt=\"image\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\nAt Right Procedure, We are going to try our best to collect the information from various sources and put out it on web, which will give one primary information about tasks, give them initial cues and if possible, key contact details, to start working. Information will be about various things you need to carry out in normal life, like getting gas connection, getting internet connections, getting licenses for various tasks, getting health insurance claims. As you search on internet or visit government websites, you wont find this information, some times you do find it but its not useful always.\r\nThough we boast, India\'s strength in solving the world\'s problem using information technology but somehow we, in India,  cannot get information on the internet which are related to our daily life. IT people who work day and night solving toughest problems in global financial market, do struggle to know the actual prices of various things in local market, and many time get cheated. We just want to work towards that goal of getting first hand, right information about how to approach in doing certain things, avoid middlemans, avoid unnecessary visits to various offices wasting your precious time and energy and at worst on waiting on customer support calls.\r\n\r\nWe do not claim that we will succeed in achieving the goal or be able to give solutions to all the problems, people face. But we thought, lets start putting this kind of information available on internet.  We are going to start by asking as many questions of how, where, what and why in daily lives, and try to put answers to these questions here. There we are getting variuos issues, we can write about, to educate or help people finding information.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><em>Mavens are \"information specialists\", or \"people we rely upon to connect us with new information.\"They accumulate knowledge, especially about the <a title=\"Marketplace\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marketplace\">marketplace</a>, and know how to share it with others.\r\n</em>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><em>-- </em><strong>Tipping Point</strong></p>\r\n\r\nYes, Maven is best term is what rightprocedure wants to be, instead of Marketplace, for us it\'s LifePlace,\r\n\r\nAs per the philosophy so far, Primary motive of this venture is not to earn money, but yearn for creating a best\r\nsource of information in cleanest possible way. So we will be avoiding online advertising which can mislead people sometime. which is going to help us in the way,  present to you cleanest possible source of information, uncluttered with online advertises and let not you distract away from the information, one come here looking for in first place.\r\n\r\nHope we able to present to you, all what you want.\r\nWish us all the best in our honest efforts !!!','Introduction',0,'','inherit','open','open','','5-revision-28','','','2008-12-09 06:49:46','2008-12-09 13:49:46','',5,'http://www.rightprocedure.com/?p=85',0,'revision','',0),(84,3,'2008-12-09 07:00:37','2008-12-09 14:00:37','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">It was when my mom was diagnosed with Cancer that we felt the need to know the right procedure to claim Medical Insurance. I asked my colleagues, some said it was easy, some said I have to be careful with agents and some said it isn’t worth all the effort that we put in.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small; font-family: Calibri;\">I got all sorts of information but didn’t get the right procedure or say the real picture. Now here started the journey to the unexplored. I called up my Insur