proof having photo and is authorized. For that you can attach<strong> Drivers License photo copy, college ID, or work ID. </strong>Then<strong> </strong>you have to attach<strong> photocopy of any address proof like ration card, Telephone/electricity bill in your name. And two photographs.</strong></li>\r\n	<li class=\"MsoNormal\">One will also need to write ward number/range/income tax assessing officer number (which you can find from the copy of the acknowledgement of the last return filed.) If you do not have that, you will have to ask your income tax department in your city, and they will give you the ward number on the form. This <a title=\"Services :: PAN :: AO Code\" href=\"http://www.tin-nsdl.com/PANaocode.asp\" target=\"_blank\">site </a> may help you for further assistance.</li>\r\n	<li class=\"MsoNormal\">After filling the form hardest part is finding the office where to fill the form. Not all the IT offices accept the forms. I am attaching the following link which should help you locate the nearest IT Service Center near your city.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">One thing you should bear in mind if you happen to submit the FORM49A at any IT Service Center run by UTIISL then you need to buy the forms from there itself as those form have a serial numbers and they wont accept any forms which does not have their series number printed on them. All forms downloaded does not have the series number.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Helpful links:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n<div class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a title=\"Department of Revenue, Ministry of Finance, Government of India\" href=\" http://www.incometaxindia.gov.in\" target=\"_blank\">Income Tax Department of India</a></div></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n<div class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a title=\"UTI Technology Services Limited - UTITSL Home\" href=\"http://%3ca%20href=%22http/www.utiisl.co.in/%22%3E%3CFONT%20face=%22Times%20New%20Roman%22%20size=3%3Ehttp:/www.utiisl.co.in\" target=\"_blank\">UTI Technology Services</a></div></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n<div class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a title=\"A repository of nationwide tax related information\" href=\" http://www.incometaxindia.gov.in\" target=\"_blank\">Tax Information Network (TIN)</a></div></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://%3ca%20href=%22http/www.tin-nsdl.com/default.asp%22%3E%3Cfont%20face=%22Times%20New%20Roman%22%20size=%223%22%3Ehttp:/www.tin-nsdl.com/default.asp\"></a></p>','Getting a PAN card',0,'','inherit','open','open','','102-revision-22','','','2009-01-12 06:06:45','2009-01-12 13:06:45','',102,'http://www.rightprocedure.com/?p=162',0,'revision','',0),(163,3,'2008-12-10 13:32:43','2008-12-10 20:32:43','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">It was when my mom was diagnosed with Cancer that we felt the need to know the right procedure to claim Medical Insurance. I asked my colleagues, some said it was easy, some said I have to be careful with agents and some said it isn’t worth all the effort that we put in.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">I got all sorts of information but didn’t get the right procedure or say the real picture. Now here started the journey to the unexplored. I called up my Insurance agent at the around 11 pm one night and asked him that it was a Corporate medical insurance, so what would be the ideal way to go about it.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><!--more--></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Okay I say “go about it” and not “claiming it” because you do not necessarily claim the money when you have a medical or health insurance.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">There are two ways to “go about it”; I was enlightened, which are as follows:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; line-height: 115%;\">Cashless</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: small;\">- You can avail this method only if you are getting the patient admitted to one of hospitals that have a tie up with your Insurance Company.</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">This is the roughly the procedure. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Our doctor suggested surgery. He said he would want to operate my mother on the following Monday. He said that the whole expense would be approximately Rs. 50,000. I had roughly one and a half day at hand. I was not tensed, I will tell you the reason after I tell you about the pre-surgery insurance formalities.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"margin-top: 0in;\" type=\"disc\">\r\n	<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo1;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Doctor has to sign the cashless claim form and write about the illness, the line of treatment and the purpose of surgery.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.5in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">In this whole procedure the <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\">Cashless card</strong> <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\">is a must</strong>. Do not buy the story of your Insurance Agent telling to mention your employee id. It doesn’t work always. </span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"margin-top: 0in;\" type=\"disc\">\r\n	<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo1;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">The form has to be submitted to the Insurance department of the Hospital which they fax to the insurance company only and only if the hospital has a tie up.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.5in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">It is advisable that you constantly keep in touch with your agent and take the 24 hour toll free number of the Insurance Company so that you can call and find out if they have received the fax from the hospital. Most of the times the hospital insurance wing doesn’t send it so make sure!</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"margin-top: 0in;\" type=\"disc\">\r\n	<li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo1;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">The Insurance Company only sends a fraction of the amount that the hospital claims. The rest of it comes after the discharge report is sent to them.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Now let me narrate my story. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">I decided to get the cashless form signed by the doctor and submit it to the Insurance wing of the hospital. However when I went to submit the form I realized the person in charge of it was not there for the day, yet I was given the assurance that things would be looked after. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Even after the assurance, I got the toll free number and the person on charge of the Hospital insurance wing. I kept on calling both the places and understood that either one of them was not being sincere. The hospital kept on telling me that they have faxed the form and Insurance Company kept on telling me that they haven’t.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">The next day was Sunday. All the administrative offices in the hospital remained closed that day. My mother was to be operated early morning; I paid Rs. 10,000 as security so that the doctors could at least start. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Moral: Get the cashless approval well in time to avoid paying the security deposit which you will face trouble to get back from the hospital authorities.</span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">It was a conservative surgery and we could take mom back home the same day. Now we faced the real trial.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">The hospital bill was in total Rs.66, 627. It wasn’t that big a deal. I called up my Insurance agent for the nth time that day and he told me that if I don’t get the formalities done within 5 pm in the evening, we would have tough time. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">The hospital would not keep the patient because it would have prepared the final bill, neither would they let release her since they would not get the Insurance Claim approval from the Insurance Company after the regular working hours.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">So here started the running around from the doctor’s cabin to the Insurance wing to my mother’s ward. The doctor had too many patients to take care of (understandable), yet he came for his regular ward visits and Okayed mom for discharge. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">The discharge approval was sent to the Insurance wing and then after approximately 50 odd calls to the Insurance Company Call Center and bickering with the Insurance wing of the hospital, we finally received the fax approving the Rs.66,000. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">Health Insurance or medical Insurance only covers expenses related to the health. They do not pay any administrative charges, like the food in the hospital, at times gloves that the doctors wear when checking or operating the patient. So that can run up to a nominal amount. <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\">It ideally should be 30% of your overall expenses.</strong></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; line-height: 115%;\">Reimbursement</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: small;\">- Reimbursement works if the hospital where you want to get the treatment done is not one of the listed hospitals with the Insurance Company.</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">It basically involves you paying the money upfront and then claiming it from the Insurance Company (getting the reimbursement).</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">I got involved in the process of reimbursement when I tried to claim the post hospitalization expenses and the Chemotherapy sessions. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Let me tell you the way which you can ideally follow when claiming for a reimbursement:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.75in; text-indent: -0.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2;\"><span style=\"font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">·</span><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\"> </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Keep all your documents carefully. The bills, prescriptions, reports and discharge certificates are essential for you to claim any hospitalization.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.75in; text-indent: -0.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2;\"><span style=\"font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">·</span><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\"> </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Insurance Company requires the originals. So definitely keep a photocopy of the originals of your documents for your reference. However if you ask they are bound to give you back the reports, after you the claim procedure over.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.75in; text-indent: -0.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2;\"><span style=\"font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">·</span><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\"> </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: small;\">In case of a deficiency of any document that is important for your claim, the Insurance Company compulsorily has to inform you about the requisite.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.75in; text-indent: -0.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2;\"><span style=\"font-family: Symbol;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">·</span><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\"> </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: small;\">The money should reach you within 21 days (this can vary with the Insurance Company).</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri;\">It is important to understand that it is integral to send reports of the tests for which you send a bill. The report is as important as the bill to establish the credibility of the claim. </span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Do not expect for the entire to be reimbursed that you have claimed because administrative charges are deducted.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">In my case the agent didn’t inform me about the deficiency neither did the claim come within 21 days. I got it after 44 long days. This situation arose in spite of me calling the agent incessantly; in fact it was as regular as every morning.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Another important thing that goes unnoticed most of the times is that the hospital <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\">charges almost become double when you avail cashless</strong>. I got to know it when my mom was going through her chemotherapy sessions. We availed for cashless for her first session and the bill was Rs.39,000. On the other hand when we started paying cash, it came down to Rs. 22,000.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">So I wish you all the luck!</span></p>','How to claim Medical/Health Insurance',0,'','inherit','open','open','','73-revision-8','','','2008-12-10 13:32:43','2008-12-10 20:32:43','',73,'http://www.rightprocedure.com/?p=163',0,'revision','',0),(164,3,'2008-12-18 08:12:02','2008-12-18 15:12:02','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">S</span></strong>o after getting NOC from Hyderabad, Andhra Pradesh, Next step was to re-register bike in Pune, I needed to deal with RTO, Pune, Maharashtra, Compare to hyd RTO, I found pune RTO to be much clumsier, full of agents, no PRO to get information with. still able to get information about what to do.</p>\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">When I went to RTO, I was surrounded by Agents, who were demandeing 2000 Rs apart from all other taxes. I think doing it yourself should be much better as it does gives you experience of working with government offices. also after doing all hard work while getting NOC from hyd, I thought this should be miniscule task. so Wanted to do it myself.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">After enquiring further, I came to know that person called Mr. Pazze handles all matters about vehicle outside Maharashtra, So I went to him and He handed me a document listing all the following. He is key person in carrying out this whole work. He will describe you whole procedure with very cool head and seems to be quite nice guy.</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>NOC from original state where vehicle belongs(in my case Hyd, AP). 2 copies original</li>\r\n	<li>RC book original, registration card</li>\r\n	<li>Vehicle Insurance</li>\r\n	<li>Invoice receipt - vehicle purchase dealer receipt</li>\r\n	<li>Entry tax , in case when you bring the vehicle before 30 months of registration date.</li>\r\n	<li>Address proof where you are staying currently with photo</li>\r\n	<li>Affidavit of non-stolen vehicle by registered owner</li>\r\n	<li>Form. No 26,27, 20,33 . you will get these forms free at rto.</li>\r\n	<li>Pencil chassis print - 5 original</li>\r\n	<li>NOC from Police Commisioner pune.</li>\r\n	<li>Registration fee- 320</li>\r\n	<li>7 % for invoice cost as registration</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nYou can refund previous paid tax by applying at Hydrabad.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">He asked me to get the affidavit on 20 Rs stamp paper. so I went outside, was inquiring abt affidavit, one person demanded me Rs 200 per affidavit and I asked some other person he was taking 100 Rs so I asked him to do the work. so while having conversation with him, I came to know that He also had reregistered his vehicle but through agents and in turn paid quite big amount to get the work done, he was happy knowing that I am doing work myself not through RTO agent.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In pt. 10. to get NOC from Police Commisioner pune., you need a letter from RTO. You will get this letter from Mr. Pazze, after showing him all the above docs, after verifying docs, he will give you a letter from RTO to Commissioner of police, You need to give it in Commissioner of police office with xerox of NOC from hyd, and residential proof. and after 7 working days you will get the NOC from Pune police. The concerned person is Mr. Chavan. He will issue you NOC in 10 minutes, if everything is ok.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Then you need to submit all of above docs to Mr. Pazze and he will check the things and you need to get assessement done from counter 30/31( i think). then after getting how much amount you need to pay, you need to pay tax at counter 23/24 (i think..). and then re submit docs along with receipt of tax payment to Mr. Pazze. He will ask you to see him after 1 and half months.</p>\r\n\r\nSo till now, it took around 2 weeks to get this much work done.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">So finally I got my docs back from RTO officer, after that I had to go to alandi office to acquire a sign from RTO officer who checks the vehicles and gives you back the paper which takes 1 hours.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Now I need to give this docs back to RTO and get New maharashtra registration number and then apply for tax refund from hyderabad office.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">I have written this blog in 2007. RTO procedure might have underwent some changes. if any of you go to RTO and find something is changed, I do request you to add comment or post link to your blog to help people who read this blog.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">please post comments, if you have any queries. also if you know anything more than whats written here, please let us know. we would like to hear from you.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"></p>','Transfer of vehicle to Pune from other state ',0,'Transfer of vehicle to pune from other state and re-registration of vehicle in pune ','inherit','open','open','','22-revision-12','','','2008-12-18 08:12:02','2008-12-18 15:12:02','',22,'http://www.rightprocedure.com/?p=164',0,'revision','',0),(165,3,'2008-12-18 08:11:22','2008-12-18 15:11:22','Here we go with first article on RightProcedure.\r\n\r\nSome three years back, I moved from Hyderabad to Mumbai. I was well settled in Hyderabad so I bought a bike there.\r\nUnder some uncertain situation I permanently transferred to Mumbai office,  so I took my bike with me\r\nto Mumbai and in few months I moved to Pune since I changed my job. As these were pretty quick moves, I didn\'t get a chance to get NOC for the bike before moving out of Hyderabad.\r\nBefore moving out, though in vain, I tried to get information about getting an NOC but didn\'t get useful information on the internet. The other sources misled me into believing that NOC is not required, so I was clueless and was happily riding my bike on the streets of Pune.\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\nUntil one fine day, a Traffic policeman stopped me and asked for NOC. I didnt have it and he asked me to pay road tax which was Rs.4000. Obviously I couldn\'t pay that much for a small mistake (\"seemingly small\") or thing which I didn\'t know. However I settled the issue by paying him whatever money I had in my wallet (I guess, some 300 rupees). Since then I started the quest of knowing the process of getting NOC so that I can peacefully ride my bike in city.\r\n\r\nI was only left with 2 options either to sell this bike in Hyd or to obtain NOC. I didnt want to sell the bike as I loved it.\r\nMy friend in Hyderabad asked one RTO agent to do this task for me but he failed to do so. There was no option but to try it myself. I went to Hyderabad with my bike and underwent the process to obtain the NOC. After lots of rounds to various police stations and RTO offices due to wrong information, I finally got the NOC.\r\n\r\nSo here is my attempt to  throw some light on the procedure to get NOC.\r\nThe procedure is as follows:\r\n\r\n1) Get a clearance certificate from traffic police - 1 day(2-3 hrs)\r\n-- need to go to police control room, near Nampalli, Hyderabad\r\n-- police were very helpful and nice there.\r\n-- no money\r\n2) Getting the challan from E-seva office\r\n-- need a xerox of RC book\r\n-- you should know that under which police station area, your address on RC card comes since you need to mention those details on the form to be submitted to E-seva office.\r\n-- knowing Telugu will help (knowing the local language always helps)\r\n-- Rs. 100 for Hyderabad and Rs 200 for Cyberabad\r\n\r\n3) E-seva people will courier this request to police station next day\r\n-- to speed-up the process, you can get the form signed from Eseva officer and take it to police station yourself. (I did this)\r\n\r\n4) Police station people will call you once they get forms from Eseva people\r\nthey will call you for verification,\r\n-- to speed-up the process, you can also go to that Police station and ask for your form, if you want to speed up process.\r\n-- dont expect much assistance here\r\n-- they might ask you for money\r\n-- knowing Telugu will help\r\n\r\n5) In some cases,they will forward this request to ACP office for that police station\r\n6) ACP office will forward this request to Police headquarters.\r\n7) Finally you need to get the no objection certificate from Crime branch, Police\r\n8) Then you need to go to RTO for getting NOC from RTA.\r\nDocuments needed\r\n- RC book\r\n- Insurance\r\n- PUC\r\n- Police Clearance\r\n- Traffic police clearance\r\n- here it takes 2 days, if requested they will do it in a single working day.\r\n\r\nIt took me 5 working days inspite of doing everthing myself (I didn\'t wait for E-seva to courier it, I myself took the signed form to the police station) , without this urgency it should take at max 2 weeks, as police verification requires atleast 1 week.\r\n\r\nI would like to dedicate this post to some people I met during this visit, and without whose help this work would not have possible at all. I dont know their names.\r\nBut I think I wont forget them.\r\nI will call them \"few good men (and women)\", people I am mentioning are the ladies at Eseva office at Kukatpalli, then officer at Cyberabad police HQ and officer at Attapur RTA. Seeing these people do good work, my belief in good people philosophy further strengthened.  And it also redoubled my own enthusiasm to work with dedication, honesty and hardwork.\r\n\r\nSo hats of \"few good men (and women)\" :)','No objection certificate for vehicle transfer',0,'No objection certificate for vehicle transfer in hyderabad, Andhra pradesh ','inherit','open','open','','19-revision-8','','','2008-12-18 08:11:22','2008-12-18 15:11:22','',19,'http://www.rightprocedure.com/?p=165',0,'revision','',0),(166,3,'2009-01-12 06:11:51','2009-01-12 13:11:51','<em>Posted by</em>: <strong>Rahul Saxena</strong>\r\nI have Karnataka Registered bike and got caught by traffic police near  university circle. I do not have the road tax paid for Maharashtra.  Traffic inspector asked me 500/- Rs as bribe  which I refused to pay as it was my New Year resolution :). So they seized my  bike and asked to go to RTO office.\r\nI went RTO office at the same day but  the responsible person was on leave. I again went next day they told me your  case have not come to RTO office yet and asked me come next day. I again went on  3rd Jan and met Mr. Bhokri from prosecution department. He asked for NOC, PUC,  Insurance, License and RC book, and asked me to fill FT form. I paid some 3650/-  INR including Maharashtra Road Tax + interest  for last 1 year (as I was driving  without paying road tax) After this they issued the letter to  traffic police  inspector to release my bike. All done in 2 hours and also got my bike on same  day after giving the letter to university circle traffic police station.\r\n\r\nOnce you pay Maharashtra Road Tax, it is not necessary to have the  Maharashtra Registration. As I suggest you won\'t do as you can drive in both  states.\r\n\r\nI would suggest you, if next time you get caught by police, just  ask them to seize your bike. (if you have brought in Maharashtra in less then a year) else interest for road  tax is very high. I paid some 850/- Rs as interest for 1 year.','Driving vehicle without re-registation in other states',0,'','publish','open','closed','','driving-vehical-without-re-registation-in-other-states','','','2009-01-14 05:42:38','2009-01-14 12:42:38','',0,'http://www.rightprocedure.com/?p=166',0,'post','',11),(167,3,'2009-01-12 06:11:17','2009-01-12 13:11:17','<em>Posted by</em>: <strong>Rahul Saxena</strong>\nI have Karnataka Registered bike and got caught by traffic police near  university circle. I do not have the road tax paid for Maharashtra.  Traffic inspector asked me 500/- Rs as bribe  which I refused to pay as it was my New Year resolution :). So they seized my  bike and asked to go to RTO office.\nI went RTO office at the same day but  the responsible person was on leave. I again went next day they told me your  case have not come to RTO office yet and asked me come next day. I again went on  3rd Jan and met Mr. Bhokri from prosecution department. He asked for NOC, PUC,  Insurance, License and RC book, and asked me to fill FT form. I paid some 3650/-  INR including Maharashtra Road Tax + interest  for last 1 year (as I was driving  without paying road tax) After this they issued the letter to  traffic police  inspector to release my bike. All done in 2 hours and also got my bike on same  day after giving the letter to university circle traffic police station.\n\nOnce you pay Maharashtra Road Tax, it is not necessary to have the  Maharashtra Registration. As I 