ion','',0),(182,2,'2009-01-12 06:13:39','2009-01-12 13:13:39','<em>Posted by</em>: <strong>Rahul Saxena</strong>\r\nI have Karnataka Registered bike and got caught by traffic police near  university circle. I do not have the road tax paid for Maharashtra.  Traffic inspector asked me 500/- Rs as bribe  which I refused to pay as it was my New Year resolution :). So they seized my  bike and asked to go to RTO office.\r\nI went RTO office at the same day but  the responsible person was on leave. I again went next day they told me your  case have not come to RTO office yet and asked me come next day. I again went on  3rd Jan and met Mr. Bhokri from prosecution department. He asked for NOC, PUC,  Insurance, License and RC book, and asked me to fill FT form. I paid some 3650/-  INR including Maharashtra Road Tax + interest  for last 1 year (as I was driving  without paying road tax) After this they issued the letter to  traffic police  inspector to release my bike. All done in 2 hours and also got my bike on same  day after giving the letter to university circle traffic police station.\r\n\r\nOnce you pay Maharashtra Road Tax, it is not necessary to have the  Maharashtra Registration. As I suggest you won\'t do as you can drive in both  states.\r\n\r\nI would suggest you, if next time you get caught by police, just  ask them to seize your bike. (if you have brought in Maharashtra in less then a year) else interest for road  tax is very high. I paid some 850/- Rs as interest for 1 year.','Driving vehical without re-registation in other state',0,'','inherit','open','open','','166-revision-7','','','2009-01-12 06:13:39','2009-01-12 13:13:39','',166,'http://www.rightprocedure.com/?p=182',0,'revision','',0),(183,2,'2009-01-14 05:20:56','2009-01-14 12:20:56','<em>Posted by</em>: <strong>Rahul Saxena</strong>\r\nI have Karnataka Registered bike and got caught by traffic police near  university circle. I do not have the road tax paid for Maharashtra.  Traffic inspector asked me 50