ding STPI) and all charges(excluding sTPI) would approximately cost you Rs.25,000.\n\nI am not sure how much it would cost if you do it on your own. I read in one of the blogs that in Delhi and Hyderabad the whole process was completed in 30 minutes after the e-Governance was launched.\n\nSoftware Technology Parks of India (STPI) is a society set up by the Department of Communication &amp; Information Technology, Government Of India in 1991, with the objective of encouraging, promoting and boosting the Software Exports from India. STPI maintains internal engineering resources to provide consulting, training and implementation services. Services cover Network Design, System Integration, Installation, Operations and maintenance of application networks and facilities in varied areas ranging from VSATs to ATM based networks.\n\nSome of the benefits under the STP scheme include Approvals are given under single window clearance mechanism.\n\nAll the imports of Hardware &amp; Software in the STP units are completely duty free, import of second hand capital goods also permitted. STP units are exempted from payment of corporate income tax for a block of 10 years (upto 2009-10).\n\nJurisdictional Directors have the powers to approve import of capital goods (net of taxes) not more than US$ 20 million. 100% Foreign equity is permitted. Re-Export of capital goods are permitted. Capital invested by Foreign Entrepreneurs Know - How Fees, Royalty, Dividend etc., can freely repatriated after payment of Income Taxes due on them if any. Call center permitted under the STPI scheme.\n\nYou can check this link for a sample of the Application form and procedure\n\n<a href=\"http://www.hyd.stpi.in/downloads/applreg.doc\" target=\"_blank\">www.hyd.stpi.in/downloads/applreg.d…</a>','procedure to get STPI license for a Pvt Ltd software company',0,'','draft','open','open','','','','','2009-07-05 18:48:59','2009-07-06 01:48:59','',0,'http://www.rightprocedure.org/?p=217',0,'post','',0),(218,1,'