 Fees, Royalty, Dividend etc., can freely repatriated after payment of Income Taxes due on them if any. Call center permitted under the STPI scheme.\n\nYou can check this link for a sample of the Application form and procedure\n\n<a href=\"http://www.hyd.stpi.in/downloads/applreg.doc\" target=\"_blank\">www.hyd.stpi.in/downloads/applreg.d…</a>','procedure to get STPI license for a Pvt Ltd software company',0,'','inherit','open','open','','217-revision','','','2009-07-05 18:38:41','2009-07-06 01:38:41','',217,'http://www.rightprocedure.org/?p=218',0,'revision','',0),(219,1,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<blockquote>saw your query regarding starting a company and accepting foreing funds.\nYou can start a pvt ltd company, the foreign partner can contribute to your company by way of equity, dividend can be paid by way of retrun to the foreing equity holder, RBI permission is a must for allotment of equity for the foreign company or individual, and the receipt of funds will have to be informed to them through your bankers in specified forms. You can maintian the Indian character of the company irrespective of the equity contribution of foreing company or foreigners.\n\n \n\nyou have started a pvt ltd company and you feel there is no activitiy that wil take place in the next two years, I think for auditor you will have to pay atleast Rs5000 to get an audit report, as for ROC you will have to file two retruns every years before OCtober 30th and November 29th assuming you close ur books in March , both the returns for filing will cost u Rs400 if filed on time, these forms will have to be certified by a professional which will cost u Rs1000, therefore to maintian a non running pvt company wil cost Rs6400 approx.\n\n \n\nThe cost of registration of a company has now been reduced and would cost you anywhere between INR 35,000-55,0000 for two DINs, Digital Signature Certificates, Name Availability Application, Government Fee, Printing of MoA and AoA, Registraiton of the Company and application for PAN.</blockquote>','',0,'','draft','open','open','','','','','2009-07-05 19:00:57','2009-07-06 02:00:57','',0,'http://www.rightprocedure.org/?p=219',0,'post','',0),(220,3,'2009-07-07 05:20:53','2009-07-07 12:20:53','<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><em>posted by: </em><strong>Sandip More</strong></p>\r\n\r\nI always believe in working out most of the things myself. When its sensitive thing like filing of one\'s income tax returns, you want to be extra cautious as generally its not advisable to share your finances with some other person when you can do it yourself.\r\n\r\nSince last two years, I was trying to file income tax returns online using Indian income tax departments website, I used to start quite enthusiastically but ends up in unsuccessful attempt. as the process was quite complex, most of the terms were unknown to me. I always believed that they should outsource it to someone. and In the end I used to outsource it to some CA.\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\nThis month we have to file income tax returns, I was in Noida away from so. I was thinking of sending documents Form16 back home and ask my brother to file returns through some CA. but may be the, Hope is the best thing in the world.  I turned to Google and searched for online filing in India.  I got to <a href=\"http://taxsmile.com\">Taxsmile</a>\r\n\r\nWebsite looked good, so I thought I would give a try as It looked better to me than kind of time I spend in Indian income tax website understanding things. I registered. registration process was simple.\r\n\r\nafter logging in, It looks very obvious process, they took me stap by step. taking personal information first.\r\n\r\nthen taking me to form where I can fill my tax details it was quite simple, exactly similler to my Form 16.\r\n\r\nI found everything pretty easy. I opted for digital signature. I just need to take application form from TaxSmile, paste photo on it and  attach PAN card xerox, address proof xerox to it. and I am done.\r\n\r\naddition to filing normal returns on Tax deduction at source on salary , it also asks for incomes from other sources like Stocks, MFs, Bank Account interests and calculates tax for you which is not included in Form 16 given  by your company and helps you to file IT returns properly and correctly to save you from future headaches.\r\n\r\nThey have good FAQ and interesting planning tools to calculate taxes.\r\n\r\nevery system has some flaws so this one too have. Actually getting documents attested is pretty good headache, instead one will go to CA. purpose of online filing, if one understand, is to do everything online and no paper work. so I think somehow they should remove this documents thing.\r\n\r\nI was getting sms\'s from MyItReturn.com, claiming they would file your income tax in 15 minutes but again\r\n\r\nthey have adoption problem, you need to download a ITR-V form and need to submit it to incometax office yourself which is kind of painful. if you anyway have to go to Income tax office, you can file your returns there directly.\r\n\r\nso still online filing of returns has scope of lots of improvement.\r\n\r\nDisclaimer: This site is not anyway related to or benefitted from Taxsmile directly or indirectly. We are not advertizing Taxsmile.','Online filing of income tax returns',0,'','publish','open','closed','','online-filing-of-income-tax-returns','','','2010-01-12 00:07:31','2010-01-12 07:07:31','',0,'http://www.rightprocedure.org/?p=220',0,'post','',0),(221,3,'2009-07-07 05:17:43','2009-07-07 12:17:43','<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><strong>Sandip More</strong></p>\n\nI always believe in working out most of the things myself. When its sensitive thing like filing of one\'s income tax returns, you want to be extra cautious as generally its not advisable to share your finances with some other person when you can do it yourself. \n\nSince last two years, I was trying to file income tax returns online using Indian income tax departments we