r\n</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Author\'s Opinion:</strong>\r\n\r\na) First, you should not fear the police. They are human like us.\r\n\r\nb) I think people pay bribes because some (corrupt )police asks for amount which is much more than actual amount, hence Charts of fine\'s or penalties should be put up at every traffic signal  and in readable sizes and languages so that person knows exact amount of fine.\r\n\r\nc) Also People unknowingly break the laws, so other lawbreaking fine\'s or penalties should be displayed.\r\n\r\nfor example, there is fine for splitting and smoking in public places, but people casually break these,\r\n\r\nand if get caught like they do caught you unaware on Dadar east platform. You try to negotiate in form of small bribe instead paying actual fine amount.','How not to pay a bribe to Police!',0,'','publish','open','open','','how-not-to-pay-a-bribe-to-police','','','2011-08-23 00:07:26','2011-08-23 07:07:26','',0,'http://www.rightprocedure.org/?p=252',0,'post','',0),(253,3,'2011-08-22 23:50:44','2011-08-23 06:50:44','<strong>Author: Sandip </strong>\n\nHindustan Times has started new series to suggesting how to stay away from corruption on personal level.\n\nI am just going to republish these articles here.\n\n<strong>Perception</strong>\n\nThe common man perceives the polliceman as someone who is out to harass him.\n\nThere have been instances where policemen have threatened people\n\nwith long-winding legal action leaving many with little optin\n\nbut to buy their way out of trouble.\n\n<strong>Remedy:</strong>\n\nNeed more interaction between police and common public.\n\nIf any policeman asks for a bribe, you car\n\n* Dial 100 and report the matter to the police control room.\n\n* Contact the Anti corruption bureau:\n\nControll room : 24921212\n\nLodge complaint online at http://acbmaharashtra.org\n\nYou can request for your identity to be protected.\n\n* If a senior police officer is asking  for bribe. You can approach his superiors.\n\n*